                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-10T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>239. Your no. 282, September 3, 1 p.m. The War Department states that it is
                    unable at this time to undertake the despatch of an American Military Mission to
                    Iran.</p>
                <pb facs="0265" n="253" xml:id="pg_253"/>
                <p>The War Department, however, has suggested the appointment of Major General C. S.
                    Ridley, an engineer officer with wide experience including duty as Governor of
                    Canal Zone and Chief of Puerto Rican Hurricane Relief Commission, to succeed
                    General Greely, who will not return to Iran. The future commitments of the War
                    Department will be based largely on the recommendations of General Ridley, who
                    is expected to make a survey of the need for a military mission.</p>
                <p>The Department is requesting the Iranian Minister here to ascertain whether the
                    designation of General Ridley is acceptable to the Iranian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
